  - [Pull Requests](#pull-requests)

## Reporting Bugs

If you encounter a bug in [Your Project Name], please follow these steps to report it:

1. **Search for Existing Issues:**
   Check the [issue tracker](https://github.com/your-username/your-repo/issues) to see if the bug has already been reported.

2. **Create a New Issue:**
   If the bug is not already reported, [create a new issue](https://github.com/your-username/your-repo/issues/new) and provide the following information:
   - A clear and descriptive title.
   - A detailed description of the bug, including steps to reproduce.
   - Information about your environment (e.g., operating system, browser version).

## Submitting Feature Requests

If you have an idea for a new feature or enhancement, please follow these steps:

1. **Search for Existing Requests:**
   Check the [issue tracker](https://github.com/your-username/your-repo/issues) to see if the feature has already been requested.

2. **Create a New Issue:**
   If the feature is not already requested, [create a new issue](https://github.com/your-username/your-repo/issues/new) and provide the following information:
   - A clear and descriptive title.
   - A detailed description of the feature, including use cases and benefits.

## Code Contribution Guidelines

### Branching

- Create a feature branch for your changes: `git checkout -b feature-branch-name`.
- Make your changes and commit them with clear and concise messages.
- Push your branch to the repository: `git push origin feature-branch-name`.
- Submit a pull request against the `main` branch.

### Coding Standards

- Follow the coding style used in the project.
- Document your code as necessary.
- Write clear commit messages.

### Pull Requests

- Provide a clear title and description for your pull request.
- Reference any related issues.
- Ensure that your branch is up-to-date with the `main` branch before creating a pull request.

Thank you for contributing to [ppm_sic]!
